Pizza wasn't a thing here when I was a kid. Before 1989 I don't think I've even heard of pizza - none was made in Poland. In the early 90s some approximations began to be offered, but they had almost nothing to do with the real thing: think thick pita-style bread with cheap cheese, ketchup and cheap ham (no, I'm not joking). As the 90s progressed, things changed. Italian style pizza finally became available, and these days it's everywhere. 

Our Polish fast food equivalent of pizza for decades was the "zapiekanka" - literally "the baked thing": a long, flat half-baguette topped with cheese and mushrooms, sometimes ham, and baked. I ate zapiekanka often as a kid in the 80s, and it's still popular, if not as much as before.

